                        <par_12
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="wcm/foundation/components/parsys">
                            <container4
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <title2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825658,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-08T09:29:04.076-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="By Richard A. Gonzalez, Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T13:44:00.972-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>On May 8, 2020, the new AbbVie was created.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;That day, AbbVie officially closed its $63-billion acquisition of Allergan to create a larger, stronger and more diversified global biopharmaceutical company. It was an acquisition that allowed us to grow in numbers and bolster our ability to improve people’s lives worldwide.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;While there was a clear business strategy for the decision to acquire Allergan and diversify our business, questions remained around how we would successfully integrate two very successful yet different businesses. Ultimately, what we learned together was the importance of executing a carefully crafted integration plan and why, above all else, employee buy-in was one of the most important pieces of the puzzle.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Now, more than two years later, the new AbbVie is a fully integrated, more diverse company and the strategic merits of the acquisition have never been clearer. Together, we have developed a more robust and diversified portfolio and expanded our research and development into new therapeutic areas to help even more patients for years to come.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;I have been in the pharmaceutical business for 40 years, and the AbbVie acquisition of Allergan was the largest acquisition I have overseen and one of the most significant in our industry. I am tremendously proud of AbbVie’s leadership team and thousands of colleagues who worked tirelessly on the integration of these two powerful companies, even as we navigated the complex challenges of a global pandemic.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Here are the three critical factors that drove the success of this transformational acquisition.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T15:11:11.259-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T15:11:11.259-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825668,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-05-15T12:09:21.981-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="1. A shared purpose is critical to bringing our distinct companies together"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"
                                    variant="noh"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T15:12:14.118-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Prior to the acquisition, AbbVie and Allergan had different areas of focus. AbbVie focused more on therapeutics in immunology, hematologic oncology and other specialty areas, while Allergan focused on aesthetics, eye care, women’s health and neuroscience. This made our companies – from a portfolio perspective – very different. It was important that our employees understand the long-term vision of bringing these two diverse companies together to create something powerful for patients.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;This was the first and perhaps most crucial step to ensuring a successful integration. We could not just rely on our leadership teams knowing that this acquisition would be transformative – our thousands of employees, across both companies, had to believe it too.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;What we found is that like AbbVie employees, Allergan colleagues shared a deep commitment to making a remarkable impact on people’s lives. This shared purpose – in addition to a tremendous amount of teamwork across all areas of both organizations – was the glue that brought our distinct companies together and what made this transaction so compelling.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;In the end, all the careful strategic planning from our combined teams was worth it. We brought together 30 brands, established strong product leadership positions in important markets, and expanded our therapeutic areas to drive long-term growth.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4>
